,"1180":"1180","Perth, Perthshire, Scotland":"Perth, Perthshire, Scotland","Kilmaurs, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Kilmaurs, Ayrshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"De","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Barclay","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name of English origin, from any of several places so called, such as Berkley in Somerset or Berkeley in Gloucestershire, both named in Old English with <i>be(o)rc</i> ‘birch’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’.","History: The surname was brought to Scotland from southwestern England in the 12th century; Walter de Berchelai or Berkelai was Chamberlain of Scotland in 1165. It was long assumed that they were from the family that held Berkeley Castle in Gloucestershire, but the historian G. W. S. Barrow (1973, <i>The Kingdom of the Scots</i>) adduced evidence that they are more probably from Berkley in Somerset."],"variants":[{"name":"Barkley","meanings":["English and northern Irish (Antrim): variant of   Barclay  .","Americanized form of German   Berkel   or of some other similar (like-sounding) German surname."]},{"name":"Barclift","meanings":["Perhaps an altered form of Scottish   Barclay  ."]},{"name":"Berkeley","meanings":["English: habitational name from one or more of the numerous places so named, such as Berkeley in Gloucestershire, named in Old English with <i>be(o)rc</i> ‘birch’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’. Compare Scottish   Barclay  .","Jewish (American): adoption of the English surname (see 1 above) in place of   Berkowitz  ."]},{"name":"Brickley","meanings":["English and Irish: metathesized form of   Barclay  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Riscinda De Barclay was born in 1118, in Scotland as the daughter of Humphrey and Mrs. Humphrey. She married Robert Cunynghame about 1149, in Perth, Perthshire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1160, in her hometown, at the age of 42."},"et":{"1118–1160":"1118–1160","1115–1180":"1115–1180","1150–1189":"1150–1189","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1118":"1118","liv abt 1125":"umbes 1125","about 1150":"umbes 1150","adult 1153":"1153","1115":"1115","about 1149":"umbes 1149","1189":"1189","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","1180":"1180","Perth, Perthshire, Scotland":"Perth, Perthshire, Scotland","Kilmaurs, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Kilmaurs, Ayrshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1118–1160":"1118–1160","1115–1180":"1115–1180","1150–1189":"1150–1189","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1118":"1118","liv abt 1125":"noin 1125","about 1150":"noin 1150","adult 1153":"1153","1115":"1115","about 1149":"noin 1149","1189":"1189","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","1180":"1180","Perth, Perthshire, Scotland":"Perth, Perthshire, Scotland","Kilmaurs, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Kilmaurs, Ayrshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1118–1160":"1118–1160","1115–1180":"1115–1180","1150–1189":"1150–1189","–Male":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1118":"1118","liv abt 1125":"environ 1125","about 1150":"environ 1150","adult 1153":"1153","1115":"1115","about 1149":"environ 1149","1189":"1189","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","1180":"1180","Perth, Perthshire, Scotland":"